'''[[astronomical]] [[unit]]''' (''plural'' '''astronomical units''')

#(''astronomy'') The [[mean]] distance from the [[Earth]] to the [[Sun]] ([[semi-major]] [[axis]] of Earth's [[orbit]]). Approximately 149,600,000 [[kilometre]]s (''symbol'' [[AU]]), used to [[measure]] [[distance]]s in the [[solar system]]. By [[definition]], when used to describe the [[motion]] of bodies within the solar system, the [[heliocentric]] [[gravitational]] [[constant]] is equal to (0.017 202 098 95)² AU³/d² (''IERS Conventions (1996), D. D. McCarthy ed., IERS Technical Note 21, Observatoire de Paris, July 1996''); [[hence]] 1 AU = 149,597,870,691±30 km.

